sch:rule.sch:assert:
The  element should not be categorized
                                    in detail with @subtype unless also categorized in general with
                                    @type

sch:rule.sch:report:
If
                                        @reason is specified on the  element and its value is
                                        "illegible", @unit and @quantity must be present, too.

attDef.desc:
indicates the bibliographic level
                                for a title, that is, whether it identifies an article, book, journal,
                                series, or unpublished material.

sch:rule.sch:report:
The
                                        @when-custom attribute cannot be used with any other
                                        att.datable.custom attributes.

The usage of
                                        @notBefore-custom|@notAfter-custom is not allowed together with
                                        @from-custom|@to-custom.
